text.section:
The county commissioners may assign to the Department:
Responsibility for construction, maintenance, repair, service, and management of:
Public works, public buildings, publicly owned water and sewerage facilities and projects, and capital projects;
Water supply facilities and projects;
Wastewater collection, treatment, and disposal facilities and projects;
Solid waste collection, recycling, and disposal facilities and projects;
Storm drainage, erosion, and sediment control facilities and projects;
Lighting for roads, highways, alleys, and other public places; or
Mosquito control facilities and programs; and
Any other function or duty that is not inconsistent with this section.

section.section:
The public local law shall provide:
For the retiring, refunding, refinancing, transfer, or assumption of any applicable outstanding bonds of the abolished entity;
For the assumption of all existing assets and liabilities of the abolished entity by the county, subject to an audit of the assets and liabilities by a certified public accountant;
For the transfer of all real and personal property of the abolished entity to the county;
For the transfer of responsibility and administration of any legally enforceable agreement between the abolished entity and another party to the county;
For the continued effect of orders, rules, and regulations of the abolished entity, until revoked or modified by the county commissioners;
That any revenues of an abolished entity remain dedicated for the purpose collected and are not transferred into the county's general fund; and
That all matters pending before the abolished entity may continue and shall be completed by the Department.
